snippet.textDisplay: I think this fusion is wonderful. .depends upon perception. .we, men, usually tend to see women/girls/ladies as the weaker sex. .we seem to see them as "merry go round" people. .we jump to conclusions, when we see someone like 'komola', who is a pretty lady and who is a dancing soul. .we tend to take her as soft, vulnerable, weak. .and this fusions points that out. .that in spite of all the dancing and prettiness and softness, a women is strong as hell. .can break through anything and find her own way. .in midst of all the obstacles. .its perception guys. .for connection, you need views, a different perspective of seeing things. .
